00:15:36.040 --> 00:15:49.340
So when I started developing an app, for some reason, I came across Flask as a solution for Python.

00:15:50.280 --> 00:15:55.420
So I started developing the app on Flask.

00:15:56.520 --> 00:16:00.980
What I like about Flask is that if you compare it,

00:16:01.720 --> 00:16:02.980
let's say you use Flask,

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:08.240
and then for the pages you use HTML, CSS, and Vanilla JavaScript.

00:16:09.500 --> 00:16:12.560
What I like is that you can deploy an app

00:16:13.840 --> 00:16:15.360
which comes from a single folder,

00:16:15.430 --> 00:16:16.820
and you've got everything there,

00:16:18.360 --> 00:16:24.660
your main flask file and then all the let's say the sub files in python with all the business

00:16:24.920 --> 00:16:32.460
logic that you can isolate in one file or or another but it's one project and then you deploy

00:16:32.460 --> 00:16:37.420
the project to GitHub and then let's say you connect GitHub to railway i'm using railway uh

00:16:37.960 --> 00:16:45.219
for for my deployment so you you connect GitHub to railway and then once you uh update your your

00:16:45.240 --> 00:16:48.800
or code in PyCharm or in Visual Studio,

00:16:49.060 --> 00:16:53.900
then you have the automatic deployment to Railway.

00:16:53.900 --> 00:16:54.880
But it's one project.

00:16:55.380 --> 00:17:01.720
Whereas if you want to decouple completely the backend

00:17:01.920 --> 00:17:04.000
from the front end, let's say you work with something

00:17:04.199 --> 00:17:06.900
like Next.js, for instance, and then you

00:17:07.220 --> 00:17:08.660
want to have a backend in something else,

00:17:09.180 --> 00:17:12.240
then you've got to have multiple instances

00:17:12.319 --> 00:17:13.199
and connect them together.

00:17:13.560 --> 00:17:15.400
It becomes more complicated.

00:17:16.020 --> 00:17:18.040
But if you want to create something simple,

00:17:18.260 --> 00:17:22.800
you can keep it simple with one single Flask web app.

00:17:22.860 --> 00:17:24.980
And that's what I've been doing so far.

00:17:26.799 --> 00:17:31.680
Most of the iJingle maker that I built,

00:17:32.700 --> 00:17:36.920
I've been building since September 23, is a Flask web app.

00:17:37.180 --> 00:17:42.920
So it's one project, one big project, but it's one project.

